      • createType

        public void createType(Environment e)
        Description copied from interface: KnownTypeTransformer
        This method is intended to introduce a new SystemC type to STATE. Optimally it creates a single Module that represents the type. There are no restrictions on how that is done. The file whose is set through the KnownTypeTransformer.setImplementation(String) method may be used.

        This method is called each time a variable declaration with the associated type occurs. The implementation of this method is responsible for preventing the creation of doubles.

        createType in interface KnownTypeTransformer
